claim.claim-text:
1. A method for facilitating annuity transactions between annuity purchasers and annuity providers via an annuities placement program accessible to the annuity purchasers and providers, the method comprising: 
facilitating annuity purchaser entry of quote solicitation information used by the annuity providers to establish a quote for an annuity; 
providing the quote solicitation information to a plurality of the annuity providers via the annuities placement program; 
facilitating annuity provider entry of at least one quote in response to the provided quote solicitation information; 
providing the quote to the annuity purchaser via the annuities placement program, wherein the provided quote is customized to the annuity purchaser's quote solicitation information; 
presenting the quotes from a plurality of the annuity providers to the annuity purchaser in a manner conducive to comparison of the quotes by the annuity purchaser; and 
facilitating selection of at least one quote by the annuity purchaser.

2. The method of claim 1, further comprising: 
establishing a discretionary group to be a contract holder for each participating annuity provider; 
establishing a master group contract for each of the participating annuity providers, wherein each of the master group contracts are written by a respective one of the participating annuity providers to the discretionary group to allow the discretionary group to be the contract holder for annuities purchased by the annuity purchasers; 
converting an annuity purchaser's qualified plan-sponsored retirement accounts to a contribution type that is available for annuity investment sponsored by the discretionary group; and 
in response to a purchase of an annuity by the annuity purchaser, issuing a certificate of participation to the annuity purchaser from the annuity provider under the terms of the master group contract of that annuity provider, and reflecting annuity terms customized to the annuity purchaser.

13. An annuity placement system comprising: 
(a) a memory to store an annuity placement program for facilitating network-based annuity transactions between annuity purchasers and annuity providers; and 
(b) a processor operating under control of the annuity placement program to perform transaction steps comprising: 
(i) facilitating annuity purchaser entry of quote solicitation information used by the annuity providers to establish a quote for an annuity; 
(ii) providing the quote solicitation information to a plurality of the annuity providers via the annuities placement program; 
(iii) facilitating annuity provider entry of at least one quote in response to the provided quote solicitation information; 
(iv) providing the quote to the annuity purchaser via the annuities placement program, wherein the provided quote is customized to the annuity purchaser's quote solicitation information; 
(v) presenting the quotes from a plurality of the annuity providers to the annuity purchaser in a manner conducive to comparison of the quotes by the annuity purchaser; 
(vi) facilitating selection of at least one quote by the annuity purchaser; and 
(vii) notifying a winning annuity provider corresponding to the annuity purchaser's selected quote, thereby facilitating implementation of an annuity customized to the annuity purchaser's request.

14. A method for facilitating annuity contract quoting between annuity purchasers and annuity providers; comprising: 
creating, by at least one annuity purchaser, an electronic annuity quote invitation; 
electronically dispatching the electronic annuity quote invitation to designated annuity providers to prompt the designated annuity providers to furnish the annuity quote; 
submitting electronic annuity quote responses, by the designated annuity providers, to the annuity purchaser in response to the electronic annuity quote invitation; 
identifying, by the annuity purchaser, a most favorable one or more of the electronic annuity quote responses; and 
electronically notifying the annuity provider who submitted the most favorable annuity quote response that the annuity purchaser is requesting to purchase an annuity with the annuity provider at terms substantially defined by the annuity quote response.

24. The method of claim 14, further comprising: 
establishing a discretionary group to be a contract holder for each participating annuity provider; 
establishing a master group contract for each of the participating annuity providers, wherein each of the master group contracts are written by a respective one of the participating annuity providers to the discretionary group to allow the discretionary group to be the contract holder for annuities purchased by the annuity purchasers; 
disassociating the annuity purchaser from a retirement plan provided by a corporate plan sponsor; 
associating the annuity purchaser with the discretionary group; and 
in response to a purchase of an annuity by the annuity purchaser, issuing a certificate of participation to the annuity purchaser from the annuity provider under the terms of the master group contract of that annuity provider, and reflecting annuity terms customized to the annuity purchaser.

25. A computer-readable medium having computer-executable instructions for facilitating annuity transactions between annuity purchasers and annuity providers, the computer-executable instructions performing steps comprising: 
facilitating annuity purchaser entry of quote solicitation information used by the annuity providers to establish a quote for an annuity; 
providing the quote solicitation information to a plurality of the annuity providers via the annuities placement program; 
facilitating annuity provider entry of at least one quote in response to the provided quote solicitation information; 
providing the quote to the annuity purchaser via the annuities placement program, wherein the provided quote is customized to the annuity purchaser's quote solicitation information; 
presenting the quotes from a plurality of the annuity providers to the annuity purchaser in a manner conducive to comparison of the quotes by the annuity purchaser; 
facilitating selection of at least one quote by the annuity purchaser; and 
notifying a winning annuity provider corresponding to the annuity purchaser's selected quote, thereby facilitating implementation of an annuity customized to the annuity purchaser's request.

26. A computer data signal embodied in a carrier wave for facilitating annuity transactions between annuity purchasers and annuity providers, the computer data signal embodied in the carrier wave comprising: 
a quote solicitation source code segment comprising program instructions for facilitating annuity purchaser entry of quote solicitation information used by the annuity providers to establish a quote for an annuity; 
a quote solicitation dispatch code segment comprising program instructions for providing the quote solicitation information to a plurality of the annuity providers via the annuities placement program; 
a quote response source code segment comprising program instructions for facilitating annuity provider entry of at least one quote in response to the provided quote solicitation information; 
a quote solicitation dispatch code segment comprising program instructions for providing the quote to the annuity purchaser via the annuities placement program, wherein the provided quote is customized to the annuity purchaser's quote solicitation information; 
a quote presentation source code segment comprising program instructions for presenting the quotes from a plurality of the annuity providers to the annuity purchaser in a manner conducive to comparison of the quotes by the annuity purchaser; 
a quote selection source code segment comprising program instructions for facilitating selection of at least one quote by the annuity purchaser; and 
a winning quote notification source code segment comprising program instructions for notifying a winning annuity provider corresponding to the annuity purchaser's selected quote, thereby facilitating implementation of an annuity customized to the annuity purchaser's request.

27. A method for facilitating pervasive availability of institutionally priced annuities for individual annuity purchasers, comprising: 
establishing a discretionary group to be a contract holder for each participating annuity provider; 
establishing a master group contract for each of the participating annuity providers, wherein each of the master group contracts are written by a respective one of the participating annuity providers to the discretionary group to allow the discretionary group to be the contract holder for annuities purchased by the annuity purchasers; 
converting an annuity purchaser's qualified plan-sponsored retirement accounts to a contribution type that is available for annuity investment sponsored by the discretionary group; and 
in response to a purchase of an annuity by the annuity purchaser, issuing a certificate of participation to the annuity purchaser from the annuity provider under the terms of the master group contract of that annuity provider, and reflecting annuity terms customized to the annuity purchaser.
